The paper deals with algorithms for selecting the $k$-th smallest item from various data structures, such as heap-ordered trees, sorted lists, and unsorted sets. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions matrices, which could indicate that it belongs to the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of soft heaps, which are a type of priority queue, suggests that the paper could also belong to the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper's focus on algorithms for selecting items could indicate that it belongs to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
